&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Shifting cultivation in the world:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Milpa in Central America.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chitemene or Tavy in Africa.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chena in Sri Lanka.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Conuco in&amp;nbsp;Venzuela.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Roca in Brazil.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Masole&amp;nbsp;in Central Africa.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ladang&amp;nbsp;in Indonesia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ray in Vietnam.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Commercial farming:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;commercial farming,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;crops are grown and animals are reared for sale in the market.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;area cultivated and the amount of capital&amp;nbsp;used is large.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Most of the work is done by machines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Commercial farming includes commercial&amp;nbsp;grain farming, mixed farming and plantation agriculture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Subsistence&amp;nbsp;farming:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subsistence farming&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;, a form of farming&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in which nearly all of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;crops or livestock raised are used to maintain the farmer and the farmer&amp;rsquo;s family&lt;/span&gt;, leaving&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;little, if any, surplus for sale or trade.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Its characteristics are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;no surplus, distress sale, less or no use of fertilizers etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Plantation farming:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Plantations are a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;type of commercial farming&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;where a single&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;crop of tea, coffee, sugarcane, cashew, rubber, banana or cotton are grown.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A large amount of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;labor and capital&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are required.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The produce may be processed on the farm itself or in nearby factories.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The development of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;transport network is thus essential&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for such farming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1) i.e. &lt;u&gt;Arunachal Pradhesh&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This state is the most &lt;strong&gt;northeastern one of India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;China and Arunachal Pradesh share a border, which is called &lt;strong&gt;McMahon Line.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Also, the Republic of China claims a large part of the state.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is even referred to as &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;South Tibet&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; by the&lt;strong&gt; People&amp;rsquo;s Republic of China.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The state also borders Bhutan, Myanmar, Assam, and Nagaland.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Ctrl + C&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + C is the universal shortcut key for copying text or objects in Windows.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is widely used in various applications such as Word, Excel, browsers, and others.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This command replicates the selected text or object to the clipboard without removing it from the original location.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Users can then paste the copied content elsewhere using the Ctrl + V shortcut.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + V:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to paste the copied or cut content from the clipboard.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + P:&lt;/strong&gt; Shortcut key for printing documents or files.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + X:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to cut selected text or objects, removing them from their original location and placing them on the clipboard.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clipboard:&lt;/strong&gt; A temporary storage area in Windows used for storing copied or cut content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Switches between open applications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pressing &lt;strong&gt;Alt + Tab&lt;/strong&gt; on a computer keyboard allows users to quickly switch between open applications or windows.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This shortcut provides a visual display of all currently running applications, enabling users to select the desired application for switching.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The functionality is supported on &lt;strong&gt;Windows operating systems&lt;/strong&gt;, making multitasking more efficient and seamless.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Holding down the &lt;strong&gt;Alt&lt;/strong&gt; key while repeatedly pressing &lt;strong&gt;Tab&lt;/strong&gt; cycles through the list of open windows in order.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This feature is particularly useful for users managing multiple tasks or applications simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Task Switching:&lt;/strong&gt; The Alt + Tab shortcut is a common example of task switching, a feature that enhances productivity by reducing the time required to navigate between open programs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Snap Assist:&lt;/strong&gt; On modern Windows versions (e.g., Windows 10/11), Snap Assist can be used alongside Alt + Tab to organize open applications into split-screen views for better multitasking.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Task View:&lt;/strong&gt; Windows also offers a &amp;quot;&amp;quot;Task View&amp;quot;&amp;quot; feature (Win + Tab) that provides a broader overview of open applications and virtual desktops, complementing Alt + Tab functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keyboard Shortcuts:&lt;/strong&gt; Keyboard shortcuts like Alt + Tab are designed to improve workflow efficiency by minimizing reliance on mouse navigation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MacOS Equivalent:&lt;/strong&gt; On MacOS, the equivalent shortcut for switching between open applications is &lt;strong&gt;Command + Tab&lt;/strong&gt;, offering similar functionality for Mac users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Margins&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Margins&lt;/strong&gt; feature in MS Word allows users to set the blank space between the text and the edges of the page.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Margins can be adjusted by navigating to &lt;strong&gt;Layout &amp;gt; Margins&lt;/strong&gt;, where predefined options like Normal, Narrow, Wide, and custom settings are available.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Changing the margins affects the document layout, helping users manage text density and page appearance efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Proper margin settings are crucial for ensuring readability, consistency, and adherence to document formatting standards, such as those required for academic or professional submissions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MS Word allows users to set margins individually for each side of the page: top, bottom, left, and right.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Page Layout Tab in MS Word:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Page Layout tab includes essential formatting options like Margins, Orientation, Size, Columns, and Page Borders.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It enables users to customize the overall appearance and structure of the document.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Margin Types:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;MS Word allows for the creation of &lt;strong&gt;gutter margins&lt;/strong&gt;, which provide extra space for binding documents.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mirror margins are used for documents intended for double-sided printing, ensuring symmetry between facing pages.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Document Orientation:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Orientation options (Portrait and Landscape) can complement margin settings to optimize document appearance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Portrait orientation is vertical, while Landscape orientation is horizontal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Page Borders vs. Margins:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While margins define blank space around text, &lt;strong&gt;Page Borders&lt;/strong&gt; add decorative or functional lines around the page&amp;rsquo;s edges.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Page Borders are customizable under the Design tab in MS Word.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance of Margins:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Proper margins improve visual appeal and help maintain a professional appearance in documents.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They are crucial for printing, ensuring text does not get cut off or overlap binding areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + S&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;284&quot; data-start=&quot;78&quot;&gt;The shortcut key combination &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + S&lt;/strong&gt; is universally used in most software applications to quickly save a file.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;400&quot; data-start=&quot;285&quot;&gt;When you press &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + S&lt;/strong&gt;, the current file or document is saved without the need to navigate through menus. This action updates any changes made to the file since the last save.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;550&quot; data-start=&quot;401&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + S&lt;/strong&gt; shortcut is supported by a wide range of applications such as &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Notepad, Photoshop&lt;/strong&gt;, and most other text editors or design tools.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;630&quot; data-start=&quot;551&quot;&gt;This shortcut is particularly useful for ensuring that work is saved frequently, preventing data loss due to unexpected events like power outages or system crashes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;710&quot; data-start=&quot;631&quot;&gt;Using &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + S&lt;/strong&gt; is a best practice in file management to maintain data integrity and avoid accidental loss of work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;830&quot; data-start=&quot;711&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is Ctrl + S.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

